Cormus is composed of regular and tightly anastomosed tubes. Water-collecting tubes are present (
Fig. 2A
).As the specimen was fragmented, it was not possible to observe the pseudoatrium. The skeleton is composed of one category of triactines, one of tetractines and diactines. Diactines are organised in tufts of two to five spicules, perpendicularly disposed in the tubes (
Fig. 2B
). Triactines are the most abundant spicules.
